{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-puzzle-js","path":"/puzzles/probability/1","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h2>Question</h2>\n<p>Two bullets are loaded into a gun's round barrel consecutively. The barrel has a capacity of 6. The gun is fired once, but no bullet is shot. Does rolling the barrel (shuffling) before next shot increase the probability of firing a bullet?</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 200px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 100%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"barrel\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/032fedc6dd58fbd8a4516432c2367ecf/56d15/1_rolling_bullet.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/032fedc6dd58fbd8a4516432c2367ecf/77dd4/1_rolling_bullet.png 50w,\n/static/032fedc6dd58fbd8a4516432c2367ecf/effb6/1_rolling_bullet.png 100w,\n/static/032fedc6dd58fbd8a4516432c2367ecf/56d15/1_rolling_bullet.png 200w,\n/static/032fedc6dd58fbd8a4516432c2367ecf/a8a0d/1_rolling_bullet.png 300w,\n/static/032fedc6dd58fbd8a4516432c2367ecf/d9f49/1_rolling_bullet.png 400w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"eager\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<h2>Hint</h2>\n<p>Since the bullets are loaded consecutively, the next shot is also constrained.</p>\n<h2>Answer</h2>\n<p>Yes, shuffling increases the probability of firing a bullet from <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mn>25</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">%</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">25\\%</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8056em;vertical-align:-0.0556em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">25%</span></span></span></span></span> to <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mn>33.</mn><mover accent=\"true\"><mn>3</mn><mo>ˉ</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">%</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">33.\\bar{3}\\%</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8368em;vertical-align:-0.0556em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">33.</span><span class=\"mord accent\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.7812em;\"><span style=\"top:-3em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">3</span></span><span style=\"top:-3.2134em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"accent-body\" style=\"left:-0.25em;\"><span class=\"mord\">ˉ</span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mord\">%</span></span></span></span></span>)</p>\n<h2>Solution</h2>\n<p><strong>Initial Misstep</strong>: If the two bullets are randomly put instead of consecutively, then, after firing one empty shot, there are <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">2</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">2</span></span></span></span></span> bullets and <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mn>5</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">5</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">5</span></span></span></span></span> total slots. The probability would be <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><mn>5</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>40</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">%</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">2/5 = 40\\%</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">2/5</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8056em;vertical-align:-0.0556em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">40%</span></span></span></span></span>, but that's not the case here.</p>\n<p><strong>Correct step</strong>: The probability of firing a bullet without a shuffle is <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mn>1</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><mn>4</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>25</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">%</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">1/4 = 25\\%</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1/4</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8056em;vertical-align:-0.0556em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">25%</span></span></span></span></span>. To understand this, imagine that the firing pin was on one of the empty slots <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mn>3</mn><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mn>4</mn><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mn>5</mn><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mn>6</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">(3, 4, 5, 6)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\">3</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">4</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">5</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">6</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></span>, and the first shot was taken, but no bullet was fired. Now assumming that the barrel rotates clockwise, the pin will move to one of these slots: <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mn>2</mn><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mn>3</mn><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mn>4</mn><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mn>5</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">(2, 3, 4, 5)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\">2</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">3</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">4</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">5</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></span>. Out of these four slots, only the slot <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">(1)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></span> has a bullet. Hence probability of firing a bullet is <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mn>1</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><mn>4</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>25</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">%</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">1/4 = 25\\%</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1/4</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8056em;vertical-align:-0.0556em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">25%</span></span></span></span></span>.\nNote that the same is true in anti-clockwise direction.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 200px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 100%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"barrel\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/5dc0a7989dc51d7c54ea9ce95f902ccb/56d15/1_rolling_bullet_a.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/5dc0a7989dc51d7c54ea9ce95f902ccb/77dd4/1_rolling_bullet_a.png 50w,\n/static/5dc0a7989dc51d7c54ea9ce95f902ccb/effb6/1_rolling_bullet_a.png 100w,\n/static/5dc0a7989dc51d7c54ea9ce95f902ccb/56d15/1_rolling_bullet_a.png 200w,\n/static/5dc0a7989dc51d7c54ea9ce95f902ccb/a8a0d/1_rolling_bullet_a.png 300w,\n/static/5dc0a7989dc51d7c54ea9ce95f902ccb/d9f49/1_rolling_bullet_a.png 400w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"eager\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<p>After the shuffle, the state is reset. There are <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mn>6</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">6</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">6</span></span></span></span></span> total slots with <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">2</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">2</span></span></span></span></span> bullets, the probabilty of firing a bullet after a shuffle is <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><mn>6</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><mn>3</mn><mo>≈</mo><mn>33</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">%</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">2/6 = 1/3 \\approx 33\\% </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">2/6</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1/3</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">≈</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8056em;vertical-align:-0.0556em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">33%</span></span></span></span></span>.</p>\n<p>Thus, shuffling does increase the probability of firing a bullet (from <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mn>25</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">%</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">25\\%</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8056em;vertical-align:-0.0556em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">25%</span></span></span></span></span> to <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mn>33</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">%</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">33\\%</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8056em;vertical-align:-0.0556em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">33%</span></span></span></span></span>)</p>\n<!-- \nThis puzzle is counter-intuitive. Even today, I'm puzzled by its answer.\nIn real life situations, I'd expect someone to say: since we already lost one slot, the probability of firing a bullet should increase. And nobody would question this conclusion.\nThis is a good reminder to always step back and think rigorously about a problem. \n-->","frontmatter":{"puzzleId":1,"difficulty":"easy","category":"probability","title":"Rolling the bullet"}}},"pageContext":{"puzzleId":1,"previousPuzzleRoute":null,"nextPuzzleRoute":"/puzzles/probability/5","category":"probability"}},"staticQueryHashes":["3649515864","764694655"],"slicesMap":{}}